---
import AddDecibelsCalculator from '../../components/AddDecibelsCalculator.astro';
import CalculatorPage from '../../components/CalculatorPage.astro';
import { socialImages } from '../../data/social';
---

<CalculatorPage
  title="Add decibels calculator | dBcheck"
  description="Combine independent sound levels correctly with logarithmic addition instead of ordinary arithmetic."
  kicker="Add Decibels Calculator"
  heading="Sound levels add as energy, not ordinary numbers."
  intro="Combine independent sound levels measured with compatible metrics and see their logarithmic total."
  socialImage={socialImages.fundamentals}
>
  <AddDecibelsCalculator />

  <Fragment slot="references">
    <section>
      <span class="kicker">How it works</span>
      <h2>Convert, add, convert back</h2>
      <p>Each decibel level is converted to a linear energy ratio, the ratios are added and the total is converted back to decibels.</p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <span class="kicker">Quick check</span>
      <h2>Equal levels add 3 dB</h2>
      <p>Two independent 80 dB sources combine to approximately 83 dB, not 160 dB. <a href="/articles/why-is-the-decibel-scale-logarithmic/">Read why the decibel scale is logarithmic</a>.</p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <span class="kicker">Important limits</span>
      <h2>Match the metrics</h2>
      <p>Do not combine incompatible averages, peaks or weightings as if they described the same quantity. Coherent phase-related signals need a different method. See the <a href="https://obis.osha.gov/dts/osta/otm/new_noise/">OSHA technical guidance</a>.</p>
    </section>
  </Fragment>
</CalculatorPage>
